# Inbox Clinic — web app environment (all values are PUBLIC; no secrets).
#
# Copy to `.env.local` and fill in. Only needed to actually sign in; the app builds
# and runs without it (the sign-in button will report it is unconfigured).

# Public Google OAuth client id for the browser PKCE / GIS token flow.
# Create one in Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials → OAuth client id
# (type: Web application). Use a project in "testing" mode with your address on the
# ≤100-user allowlist, so the gmail.readonly restricted scope needs no verification.
# See docs/design-gmail-integration.md.
VITE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
